 {"id":"bd-3ar8v.2.2","title":"[Phase 1] Implement write-behind autosave queue with bounded batching","description":"Introduce a queue-based persistence pipeline with controlled flush cadence and backpressure.","design":"Implement write-behind autosave queue with bounded batch policy and backpressure handling. Flush triggers are policy-based and explicit.","acceptance_criteria":"1) Queue implementation supports coalescing multiple mutations per flush. 2) Backpressure behavior is defined and tested. 3) Flush lifecycle is observable through instrumentation. 4) Shutdown path guarantees final flush semantics according to selected durability mode.","notes":"Reasoning: batching is the primary lever for reducing write amplification while preserving user-visible correctness.

